Description: Lower body sherd of Attic Black figure pottery cylinder lekythos; exterior: incised decoration consisting of circle pattern in added red with black dot from the bottom of a palmette; below, part of two concentric black bands.
Curator's comments: The sherd possibly belongs to the same vase as British Museum 2011,5009.132. For parallels, see British Museum 1952,0204.7 from Kamiros.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0806) (Phase 1)
